2. What does setState() do?
3. When would you use Stack instead of Column?',2,1,'2026-02-16 07:11:08'),
(35,6,'State Management & Navigation','## State Management in Flutter

As apps grow, managing state across multiple screens becomes complex. Flutter offers several state management solutions.

## Provider (Recommended for Beginners)

```dart
// 1. Create a ChangeNotifier
class CartProvider extends ChangeNotifier {
  List<String> _items = [];
  List<String> get items => _items;
  int get count => _items.length;

  void addItem(String item) {
    _items.add(item);
    notifyListeners(); // Rebuild listening widgets
  }

  void removeItem(String item) {
    _items.remove(item);
    notifyListeners();
  }
}

// 2. Wrap app with ChangeNotifierProvider
MultiProvider(
  providers: [ChangeNotifierProvider(create: (_) => CartProvider())],
  child: MyApp(),
)

// 3. Read state in any widget
final cart = Provider.of<CartProvider>(context);
Text(''Cart: ${cart.count} items'');
```

## Navigation

```dart
// Push a new screen
Navigator.push(
  context,
  MaterialPageRoute(builder: (context) => DetailScreen(id: 5)),
);

// Pop back
Navigator.pop(context);

// Named routes
Navigator.pushNamed(context, ''/profile'', arguments: {''userId'': 42});

// Bottom navigation
BottomNavigationBar(
  currentIndex: _selectedIndex,
  onTap: (index) => setState(() => _selectedIndex = index),
  items: [
    BottomNavigationBarItem(icon: Icon(Icons.home), label: ''Home''),
    BottomNavigationBarItem(icon: Icon(Icons.person), label: ''Profile''),
  ],
)
```

## Practical Task

